SEIZURES, SEALIONS - CALIFORNIA USA
===================================
[see Penguins - South Africa (5) archive.960112]
jkmazet@ucdavis.edu (Jonna Mazet) wrote:
>I am a Wildlife Veterinarian for the California Department of Fish and
>Game's Office of Oil Spill Prevention and Response and respond to oil
>spill incidents as well as do research in oil spill related wildlife
>epidemiology. While, I do not recall this type of behavior in birds
>exposed to petroleum products, we are investigating the cause of
>seizuring in California sea lions which may have been exposed to a
>diesel-like product.
>Let me know if I can help.
With the growing recognition of the importance of morbillivirus infections
in marine mammals, can you tell us whether a viral infection has been ruled
out?
Jack
